trend_summary: Built-up area grows gradually, mainly near the northern coast and along a new inland road. Forest is thinned by scattered clear-cuts and small farms, yet still dominates most of the peninsula. Shoreline morphology is stable with limited dune work. Overall pattern stays rural and low-density despite modest settlement infill.
notable_changes: Northern coastal town expanded, filling gaps and extending its street grid inland.
New access roads cut through central forest, triggering ribbon housing development.
Patchy forest clearings appear west of the lagoon for small farms or resource extraction.
Visible vegetation regeneration on previously cleared southern tracts suggests land-use rotation.
